  "abstract": "Improved Spanish peanut (Arachis hypogaea L. subsp. fastigiata\r\nvar. vulgaris) germplasm lines ICGV 92196 (Reg. no. GP-92, PI\r\n599344), ICGV 92206 (Reg. no. GP-93, PI 599345), ICGV 92234\r\n(Reg. no. GP-94, PI 599346), and ICGV 92243 (Reg. no. GP-95,\r\nPI 599347) were bred at the International Crops Research Institute\r\nfor the Semi-Arid Tropics (ICRISAT) Asia Center (IAC), Patancheru,\r\nA.P., India. These four lines were released as earlymaturing,\r\nhigh-yielding germplasm by the Plant Materials Identification\r\nCommittee of ICRISAT in 1996.",
